                <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>  Manager approval process: Managers should be able to approve or reject employee leave requests. This could involve a workflow where the manager receives an email or notification of the request and then logs into the system to approve or reject the request.</li>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i> Leave calendar: The system could provide a calendar view of employee leave requests and approved leaves. This would allow managers to see when employees are planning to be out of the office and plan accordingly.</li>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>Leave balances: The system should track employee leave balances and show employees how much leave they have available for each type of leave. This would prevent employees from taking more leave than they are entitled to.
</li>

